claim.claim-text:
A gas turbine combustor comprising:
a combustion chamber (50) that burns a fuel and air to generate combustion gases (102);
a fuel header (40) with a plurality of fueling nozzles (31) disposed thereupon to inject the fuel;
an air injection hole plate (38) with a plurality of air injection holes (32) formed therein to deliver to the combustion chamber (50) the air along with the fuel injected from the fueling nozzles (31);
cross fire tubes that each transport the combustion gases (102) to an adjacent combustor and ignite the adjacent combustor during gas turbine ignition; and
supports (15) for fixing the air injection hole plate (38) to the fuel header (40),
wherein the supports (15) are provided so as to be of the same phase as that of the cross fire tubes.
